            <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
              <summary class="font-medium cursor-pointer">What is the difference between resident and nonresident city tax rates?</summary>
              <p class="mt-2 text-gray-700">Most Michigan city income tax ordinances use a <strong>higher rate for residents</strong> and a <strong>lower rate for nonresidents</strong>. Residents are typically taxed on all taxable income, while nonresidents are taxed only on income earned in that city. The calculator lets you switch between resident and nonresident to see the impact.</p>
